==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tiffin
<hw>Tif"fin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Properly,
<ets>tiffing</ets> a quaffing, a drinking. See <er>Tiff</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A lunch, or slight repast between breakfast
and dinner; -- originally, a Provincial English word, but introduced
into India, and brought back to England in a special sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiffish</ent>⟦br⟧
